TITLE: Wife of Mark Meadows appears to have used invalid address on North Carolina voter forms
SUMMARY: Debra Meadows, the wife of former congressman and Trump chief of staff Mark Meadows, signed voter forms attesting she resided at a Macon County, North Carolina, mobile home that reports indicate the couple never lived in.

TITLE: Questions swirl over whereabouts of Russia's defense minister
SUMMARY: Speculation mounted over the whereabouts of Defense Minister Sergei Shoigu on Thursday as the Kremlin spokesperson declined to comment on media reports that he had health problems.

TITLE: Top Pentagon officials have not spoken to their Russian counterparts since invasion of Ukraine began
SUMMARY: Senior Russian military leaders have declined calls from their US counterparts since before the invasion of Ukraine began, a Pentagon spokesman said Thursday.

TITLE: Supreme Court says Texas death row inmate can have spiritual adviser 'lay hands' and pray aloud during his execution
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court ruled on Thursday that a Texas death row inmate could have his spiritual adviser pray aloud and "lay hands" on him during his execution, establishing new guidelines that will govern similar requests in other prisons across the country.

TITLE: In old family photographs, a South African artist reenacts her late mother's life
SUMMARY: In each of her projects Lebohang Kganye uses the photograph like a theater stage, building the cast, props and environments to tell stories about her family.

TITLE: 'What happens when women reclaim the spaces that are designed to exclude them?' Oscar-nominated filmmaker Rintu Thomas speaks to CNN
SUMMARY: One of the directors of the highly acclaimed Indian documentary, "Writing with Fire," talks to As Equals editor, Eliza Anyangwe about her film and what she learned from its protagonists.

TITLE: Analysis: Ketanji Brown Jackson demonstrated a serious and thoughtful demeanor as she faced offensive questioning from some Republicans
SUMMARY: Beyond the hyperbole and theatrics that have punctuated this week's Senate Judiciary Committee hearings, a portrait of Ketanji Brown Jackson as jurist has begun to emerge.

TITLE: Bad Bunny is offering a chance to stay in his luxe trailer
SUMMARY: Bad Bunny will open the trailer doors to his distinct 53-foot matte black semi-truck for an overnight Airbnb stay.

TITLE: Russia's days as an energy superpower are coming to an end
SUMMARY: Russia's role in the European and global energy system has been shaken. This is a profound shift that will mark the end of Russia as an energy superpower.

TITLE: Kyrie Irving appears set to play home games in New York again, with mayor expected to lift vaccine mandate for athletes
SUMMARY: Brooklyn Nets star Kyrie Irving's six-month prohibition from playing home games over his vaccination status appears to be coming to an end.

TITLE: Western leaders hold snap summits on Russia's war in Ukraine with refugee and sanctions announcements
SUMMARY: Leaders attending a slew of emergency summits here Thursday were working to settle on the next phase of their response to Russia's war in Ukraine, with new US sanctions and refugee assistance among the steps emerging from the snap talks.

TITLE: Tax penalties are a waste of your money. Here's how to avoid them
SUMMARY: Unless you enjoy throwing money away, you'll want to do all you can to avoid being hit with tax penalties and interest if you end up owing money to the IRS on your 2021 tax return.

TITLE: Chechens are fighting in Ukraine. But are they more hype than help for Vladimir Putin?
SUMMARY: Footage of a firefight that surfaced on social media earlier this week appears to show an unusual group of combatants: Apparent Chechen volunteers fighting on the side of Ukraine against Russia.

TITLE: US to welcome 100,000 Ukrainian refugees
SUMMARY: The United States will welcome up to 100,000 Ukrainians and others fleeing Russia's aggression, a senior administration official announced Thursday.

TITLE: Travel to Turkey during Covid-19: What you need to know before you go
SUMMARY: If you're planning to travel to Turkey, here's what you'll need to know and expect if you want to visit during the Covid-19 pandemic

TITLE: Mortgage rates keep climbing
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates continued to rise amid fears of inflation and geopolitical uncertainty. The 30-year fixed-rate mortgage averaged 4.42% in the week ending March 24, up from 4.16% the week before, according to Freddie Mac.

TITLE: Weekly jobless claims fall to a nearly 53-year low
SUMMARY: Just 187,000 people in the United States filed for initial weekly unemployment benefits last week, lower than economists' expectations of 210,000, according to data released Thursday by the Department of Labor.

TITLE: Ukrainians claim to have destroyed large Russian warship in Berdyansk
SUMMARY: Ukrainian armed forces have said they destroyed a large Russian landing ship at the port of Berdyansk in southern Ukraine on Thursday.

TITLE: The surprising reason why Vikings abandoned a successful settlement
SUMMARY: For years, researchers have sought to understand why Vikings abandoned one of their settlements in Greenland after centuries of success. New research suggests the cold wasn't a factor, but another climate issue proved to be too difficult.

TITLE: North Korea fires first suspected ICBM since 2017
SUMMARY: North Korea has fired what is believed to be its first intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM) in more than four years as Western leaders gather in Brussels for a security summit.

TITLE: BlackRock says Russia's war in Ukraine is the end of globalization
SUMMARY: Russia's invasion of Ukraine has ended globalization as we know it, says the head of BlackRock, the world's largest asset manager.

TITLE: Qatar will stand 'in solidarity' with European countries during energy crisis
SUMMARY: Qatar will stand "in solidarity with Europe" and will keep natural gas flowing there, even if other customers are willing to pay more, Qatari Energy Minister Saad Al Kaabi told CNN's Becky Anderson in an exclusive interview on Thursday.

TITLE: Ketanji Brown Jackson's confirmation hearing: Day 4
SUMMARY: The Senate Judiciary Committee is holding its final day of confirmation hearings for President Biden's Supreme Court nominee Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson. Watch live and follow here for the latest news updates.

TITLE: World leaders meet over Russia's invasion in Ukraine
SUMMARY: World leaders are in Brussels Thursday to attend emergency summits as they seek to align their responses to Russia's brutal invasion of Ukraine. Follow here for live news updates.

TITLE: Sunrise Movement endorses progressive Democrats Summer Lee, Nida Allam and Erica Smith for Congress
SUMMARY: Sunrise Movement, the youth-led climate activist group, on Thursday announced its endorsements of Summer Lee in Pennsylvania's 12th Congressional district, Nida Allam in North Carolina's 4th Congressional district and Erica Smith in North Carolina's 1st Congressional district, further bolstering progressive support behind the three Democratic candidates for the US House of Representatives.

TITLE: Here's why gas is $6 a gallon in California, even as prices fall elsewhere
SUMMARY: For many drivers in California, the possibility of paying $6 a gallon for gas is no longer something to worry about down the road. It's already a reality.

TITLE: Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson may have set a new standard for future nominees
SUMMARY: After day three of hearings in the Senate Judiciary Committee, Adam J. White writes that Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson may have set a new standard for answering the committee's questions by emphasizing the importance of constitutional text as a restraint on judicial discretion.
